at is otherwise quite scattered in the literature and including some important new results, it will serve graduate students and researchers interested in Hamiltonian dynamics and celestial mechanics. The contributors are Dieter Schmidt, Ernesto Pérez-Chavela, Mark Levi, Plácido Táboas and Jack Hale, Jair Koiller et al., Hildeberto Cabral, Florin Diacu, and Alain Albouy. The topics covered include central configurations and relative equilibria for the N-body problem, singularities of the N-body problem, the two-body problem, normal forms of Hamiltonian systems and stability of equilibria, applications to celestial mechanics of Poincaré's compactification, the motion of the moon, geometrical methods in mechanics, momentum maps and geometric phases, holonomy for gyrostats, microswimming, and bifurcation from families of periodic solutions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCelestial mechanics. 0aMany-body problem. 0aMechanics. 7aSCIENCE / Astronomy.2bisacsh  aAction integral.  aAdiabatic phases.  aAngular momentum.  aAutonomous system.  aBehavior at infinity.  aBifurcation diagram.  aBilliards on the sphere.  aBounded orbits.  aCenter of mass.  aChaotic phenomena.  aCharacteristic system.  aCoefficient topology.  aCollision singularity.  aDegenerate configuration.  aDraconitic month.  aDual cones.  aEccentric anomaly.  aEccentricity.  aEnergy ellipsoid.  aExternal potential.  aFast variables.  aFirst integral.  aFoucault pendulum.  aGauss map.  aGeodesic torsion.  aHamiltonian function.  aHamiltonian mechanics.  aHerpolhode.  aIgnorable variables.  aInertia ellipsoid.  aInternal potential.  aJacobi coordinates.  aLagrange bracket.  aLagrangian formalism.  aLocked inertia tensor.  aMean anomaly.  aMechanical connection.  aMutual distances.  a